init_text:
Are We Being Bad Citizens If We Don't Keep Up With the News?

In your opinion, are we being bad citizens if we don't keep up with the news? Do you think all people have some responsibility to know what is going on in the world? Does engaging with current events actually do anything at all? Why do you think the way you do?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: in a world that is becoming increasingly more connected and having less and less barriers, you are in direct relation with everything that happens.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: to know what is happening because their actions and the way they live their lives have a direct impact with the people that surrounds them.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: So yes, each of us do have some responsibility to know what is happening in the world, to know the communities we are a part of and it

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: We wouldn't know about the social injustices that exist in other places or the natural disasters that affect us all.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I think it is important that everyone keeps up with world events because we all live among each other, and have a responsibility to ourselves and others to know
